<number box="[1295,1356,1546,1572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1866.0">1866</number>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 
<number box="[1399,1431,1546,1572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="27.0">27</number>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,258,1584,1610]" name="Spain" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Hispania</collectingCountry>
, Aranjues, D. Lethierry, 
<emphasis box="[547,617,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">ferula</emphasis>
” is a female pinned through the right elytron (elytra hardly separated, fore right leg missing), bearing the handwritten label: “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Chv." authorityName="Chv." box="[802,1048,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita">
<emphasis box="[802,985,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Lixus hypocrita</emphasis>
Chv.
</taxonomicName>
aranjeus, ombellifera a fl. jaune, Lett. sp.”, and fitting the description with 
<typeStatus box="[661,713,1658,1684]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
locality as Aranjuez. It is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[1264,1374,1658,1684]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">lectotype</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus box="[161,297,1696,1722]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, Ƥ, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chev., Gultekin" authorityName="Chev., Gultekin" box="[345,721,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita">
<emphasis box="[345,528,1696,1721]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Lixus hypocrita</emphasis>
Chev., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[781,846,1696,1722]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2006.0">2006</number>
”.
</paragraph>
