<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1509,1871]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,317,1733,1759]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,509,1733,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita">
<emphasis box="[325,509,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Lixus hypocrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1781" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1781" box="[664,1055,1733,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrus">
<emphasis box="[664,844,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Lixus cylindrus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 
<number box="[987,1047,1733,1759]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1781.0">1781</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Petri, 1904" authorityName="Petri" authorityYear="1904" box="[1114,1406,1733,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[1114,1265,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Lixus obesus</emphasis>
Petri, 
<number box="[1344,1406,1733,1759]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
. It is smaller than 
<taxonomicName box="[329,440,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[329,440,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">L. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its punctures are wider and deeper along the elytral base, its rostrum is more curved and cylindrical. The rostrum of 
<taxonomicName box="[535,682,1808,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita">
<emphasis box="[535,682,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">L. hypocrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is shorter than that of 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1100,1808,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrus">
<emphasis box="[956,1100,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">L. cylindrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and on the elytra there is a transverse band near the apex but no longitudinal white bands.
</paragraph>
